What is the result?

    A.  100
        100
        1000
    B.  101
        101
        1000
    C.  1001
        100
        1000
    D.  1001
        1001
        1000

Ans.
    (C.)

Google:
    Define the terms pass-by-reference and pass-by-value:
        Pass-by-reference: When a method is called, the method arguments reference the same variable in memory as the caller.
        Pass-by-value: When a method is called, the caller passes a copy of the argument variables to the method
            resulting in two values in memory.